Date: Fri, 21 Jan 2022 15:46:23 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cs: fix refcount leak of a dma_fence obj
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: dfced44f122c500004a48ecc8db516bb6a295a1b
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
References: git-fixes CVE-2022-49137 bsc#1238155

This issue takes place in an error path in
amdgpu_cs_fence_to_handle_ioctl(). When `info->in.what` falls into
default case, the function simply returns -EINVAL, forgetting to
decrement the reference count of a dma_fence obj, which is bumped
earlier by amdgpu_cs_get_fence(). This may result in reference count
leaks.

Fix it by decreasing the refcount of specific object before returning
the error code.

Reviewed-by: Christian KÃ¶nig <christian.koenig@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Xin Xiong <xiongx18@fudan.edu.cn>
Signed-off-by: Xin Tan <tanxin.ctf@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cs.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cs.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cs.c
index 06d07502a1f6..a34be65c9eaa 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cs.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cs.c
@@ -1509,6 +1509,7 @@ int amdgpu_cs_fence_to_handle_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
 		return 0;
 
 	default:
+		dma_fence_put(fence);
 		return -EINVAL;
 	}
 }
